I can imagine some practical usefulness in being able to redact in white, in that harcopy printouts of a large, heavily redacted document can really burn through toner/ink.<br>
<br>
Being able to choose a color might also be useful&nbsp;in flagging/color-coding redaction efforts by&nbsp;&quot;who did it&quot;&nbsp;or&nbsp;for what purpose the redactions&nbsp;were done.&nbsp; Or, some may wish to say, redact in chartreuse, just for pure aesthetic desire.&nbsp;&nbsp;I guess my&nbsp;answer and personal preference is yes, color choice would be good.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
